Looking at your code, there are two specific bugs causing these issues.

---

## Bug 1 — Cooldown timer is frozen (shows static text, not counting down)

`calculateRemainingCooldown` is called inside `remember(task.nextAvailableAt)` which only recalculates when `nextAvailableAt` changes — never while time passes. The string is computed once and frozen.

**Fix:** Replace the static `remember` with a `produceState` that ticks every second:

```kotlin
// Replace this:
val remainingTime = remember(task.nextAvailableAt) {
    calculateRemainingCooldown(task.nextAvailableAt)
}

// With this:
val remainingTime by produceState(
    initialValue = calculateRemainingCooldown(task.nextAvailableAt),
    key1 = task.nextAvailableAt
) {
    while (true) {
        delay(1000)
        value = calculateRemainingCooldown(task.nextAvailableAt)
        if (value.isEmpty()) break // stop ticking once expired
    }
}
```

Do the same for `timeUntilReset`:
```kotlin
val timeUntilReset by produceState(
    initialValue = calculateTimeUntilReset(task.nextResetTime),
    key1 = task.nextResetTime
) {
    while (true) {
        delay(60000) // reset time is less urgent, tick every minute
        value = calculateTimeUntilReset(task.nextResetTime)
    }
}
```

